spacing: xs(4px), sm(8px), md(16px), lg(24px), xl(32px), 2xl(48px), 3xl(64px), 4xl(80px)
radius: sm(8px), md(12px), lg(16px), xl(20px), full(9999px)
transitions: fast(150ms), base(200ms), slow(300ms)
```

### CSS Variables (src/frontend/lib/theme/tokens.ts)
```
cssVars:
  colors:
    background: --color-background
    surface: --color-surface
    ... (all color tokens mapped to CSS vars)
  fonts:
    display: --font-display
    body: --font-body
    serif: --font-serif
  neuron:
    color: --neuron-color
    secondary: --neuron-secondary
    opacity: --neuron-opacity
```

### Theme Context (src/frontend/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx)
- Provides: `resolved` ("light"|"dark"), `toggle` function
- Persists theme in localStorage
- Uses `prefers-color-scheme` as default
- Anti-flash strategy: Sets `data-theme` on documentElement

### Theme Usage
- Layout.tsx: Uses theme to set headerBg, navLinkColors, footerColors, etc.
- UI Components: Use `cn()` utility with dark mode variants (e.g., `dark:bg-cybin-navy`)
- Custom Properties: Tokens converted to CSS vars via `varValue()` helper

## 3. SEO Critical Path Index

### Core SEO Files
- `useSeo` (src/frontend/hooks/useSeo.ts)
  - Updates: document.title, meta description, canonical link, OG/Twitter tags
  - Critical: Canonical URL always uses VERIFIED_ORIGIN (https://cybin-enterprises-1.vercel.app)
  - OG Image: Defaults to /assets/cybin-logo.png?v=3 with theme-aware handling

- `JsonLd` (src/frontend/src/components/JsonLd.tsx)
  - Generates: JSON-LD schema for Organization, WebSite, BreadcrumbList
  - Critical: Must match canonical URL and business info

### SEO-Critical Pages
- All pages use `useSeo` hook (HomePage, AboutPage, ContactPage, etc.)
- Canonical URLs: Must be absolute and match VERIFIED_ORIGIN
- Meta Tags: Title, description, og:title, og:description, og:url, og:image

### SEO Dependencies
- Route Changes: useSeo runs on every route change via useEffect
- Theme Changes: OG image may need regeneration if theme affects image
- Build Time: Static export (if used) must preserve SEO tags

## Reference ID System

### File Header Format
Every file should contain:
```
// Reference ID: <module>.<file>.<purpose>
// Dependencies: <list of file references>
```

### Example
```
// Reference ID: src.frontend.hooks.useSeo
// Dependencies: src.frontend.lib.router, src.frontend.contexts.ThemeContext
```

### Reference ID Structure
- `<layer>.<subpath>.<filename>`
- Layers: app, pages, widgets, features, entities, shared
- Example: `shared.ui.button` for src/frontend/components/ui/button.tsx

## Critical "Do Not Touch" List

1. SEO Canonical Logic (useSeo.ts lines 42-43)
   - Always uses VERIFIED_ORIGIN for canonicals
   - Changing breaks SEO consistency

2. Theme Detection Anti-Flash (ThemeContext.tsx)
   - Uses `prefers-color-scheme` + localStorage
   - Sets `data-theme` on documentElement before render

3. Animation Z-Index Management
   - NeuronCanvas uses absolute positioning
   - TickerBar uses fixed positioning (z-index: 60)
   - Cookie consent uses fixed positioning (z-index: 60)

4. StorageClient Hash Validation
   - Strict SHA-256 format validation
   - Changing breaks file upload/download

5. Route Matching Logic (lib/router.tsx)
   - Custom hash-based router
   - Changing breaks client-side navigation

## Change Checklists

### "I want to add a new page"
1. Create page in /pages directory
2. Add route to App.tsx (or create route component)
3. Add useSeo hook with appropriate title/description/canonical
4. Add link to navigation menu in Layout.tsx
5. Add to sitemap if static export

### "I want to change a color"
1. Update tokens.ts (light/dark sections)
2. Update cssVars if new token needed
3. Update tailwind.config.js if using in CSS
4. Check all usages in components (should auto-update via token reference)
5. Verify contrast ratios for accessibility

### "I want to add an animation"
1. Determine trigger (scroll, click, theme change)
2. For scroll: use useScrollAnimation/useScrollReveal hooks
3. For theme: use useTheme hook and conditionally apply classes
4. For complex motion: use framer-motion (motion/react)
5. Add to animation dependency graph in .repository-map.md
6. Test in both light and dark modes

## Layer Definitions (FSD)

/app: Global setup (routing, global styles, theme providers)
- src/frontend/App.tsx
- src/frontend/main.tsx
- src/frontend/index.css
- src/frontend/lib/router.tsx
- src/frontend/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx

/pages: Full page compositions
- src/frontend/components/pages/*.tsx
- src/frontend/components/pages/home/*.tsx

/widgets: Complex components (Theme-Aware Navbar, Animated Hero)
- src/frontend/components/layout/PageHero.tsx
- src/frontend/src/components/Layout.tsx (header/footer)
- src/frontend/components/ui/menubar.tsx
- src/frontend/components/ui/navigation-menu.tsx

/features: Business logic (Dark/Light Mode toggle, User Auth)
- src/frontend/hooks/useThemeColors.ts
- src/frontend/hooks/useSiteSettings.ts
- src/frontend/hooks/useInternetIdentity.ts
- src/frontend/hooks/useActor.ts

/entities: Domain data (Product list, Industry-specific data)
- src/frontend/data/blogPosts.ts
- src/frontend/data/industries.ts
- src/frontend/components/pages/home/IndustryTicker.tsx (ALL_INDUSTRIES)

/shared: Reusable UI, SEO utilities, Animation presets, API clients
- src/frontend/components/ui/*
- src/frontend/hooks/*
- src/frontend/lib/*
- src/frontend/contexts/*

